---
Source:
  - Title: The Essential Mystics, Poets, Saints and Sages
    ISBN: 978-1571746931
Page: 288
Author: Aldous Huxley
---
One's desire for God, if uncontrolled,
can obstruct the soul from reaching its goal.
The desite for God must come from a place of stillness.
It must become passive,
yet embody the intensity of one's heart and mind.
